  object
  (str sectionId) (str 9621)
  (str sectionNo) (str 1)
  (str orderNo) (int 1)
  (str title) (str `Short title.`)
  (str content) (str `This Act may be called the High Courts (Seals) Act, 1950.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00004_195007_1517807318859&sectionId=9621&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00004_195007_1517807318859)
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 9622)
  (str sectionNo) (str 2)
  (str orderNo) (int 2)
  (str title) (str `Seals of High Courts.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) Every High Court in a ^1
[State] shall have and use, as occasion may
arise, a seal bearing a device and impression of the Asoka capital within an exergue or label surrounding
the same, with the following inscriptions at convenient places, namely, “THE SEAL OF THE HIGH
COURT AT (or OF) ..............”, followed by the name of the seal of the High Court or the name of the
State, as the case may be, and “Satyameva Jayate” in Devanagari script.

(2) Every Court of the Judicial Commissioner for a ^2
[Union territory] shall have and use, as occasion
may arise, a seal similar to the seal of a High Court in a ^3
* * * State, but with the first inscription reading
“THE SEAL OF THE JUDICIAL COMMISSIONER'S COURT FOR .......................” followed by the
^4
[name of the Union territory].

(3) The provisions of this shall supersede any provision contrary thereto or inconsistent therewith
contained in any Letters Patent, Order, direction or other law relating to the use of seals by High Courts.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for "Part A State or Part B State".

2. Subs., ibid., for "Part C State".

3. The word and letter "Part A" omitted, ibid.

4. Subs., ibid., for "name of the State".`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00004_195007_1517807318859&sectionId=9622&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00004_195007_1517807318859)
